description: Use signalos validate-worktree-sync before merge/release worktree gates.
globs: [".signalos/worktree-sync/**", ".signalos/evidence/worktree-sync/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# validate-worktree-sync wiring rule

Run `signalos validate-worktree-sync --require-clean --json` before treating a
worktree as merge- or release-ready.

- Git state must be readable without mutation.
- A snapshot must be persisted.
- Dirty non-SignalOS files are blockers when `--require-clean` is used.
- SignalOS bookkeeping under `.signalos/` is not counted as product dirt.
